  "title": "Tapping for body-level wired",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute bedtime script for when your body won't stand down even though you are exhausted.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice for the physical state of being wired at bedtime: the restlessness that sits in the legs and shoulders, the shallow breath, the body that won't settle even though you are tired. Use in bed or just before.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 3 of SLEEP: A 30-Day Tapping Intensive to Fall Asleep Faster and Wake Energised (Rebecca J Page, 2025), \"Calm the body.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
  "body": {
